text: Frederick Simpson may refer to: * Frederick Simpson (boxer) (1916–1975), British boxer who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics * Frederick Simpson (athlete) (1878–1945), Mississauga Ojibway Canadian athlete * Frederick Arthur Simpson (1884–1974), historian and fellow of Trinity College, Cambridge * Fred Simpson (politician) (1886–1939), British Labour Party politician, MP for Ashton-under-Lyne 1935–1939 * Freddy Simpson (1883–?), English footballer for Lincoln City * Fred Simpson (fl. 1999), coach for Rangers A.F.C. in Christchurch, New Zealand
title: Frederick Simpson
